      "message": "[error] Line 704: Potential self-deadlock. conferenceFormatChanged() acquires std::lock_guard lock(mutex_) at the top of the function, then calls restartSender() here (and again at the setBitrate() branch below). In this file restartSender() takes its own std::lock_guard lock(mutex_); since mutex_ is a non-recursive std::mutex, invoking it while the lock is already held will deadlock. Note the existing setNewBitrate()/RTCP-adaptation callers reach restartSender() WITHOUT holding mutex_, which is why the same pattern is safe there but not here. Fix by not holding the lock across the restart: compute the new bitrate/pixel state under the lock, then release it before calling restartSender()/sender_-\u003esetBitrate(), e.g. move the restart logic out of the locked scope (or use a scoped block for the lock). Please confirm restartSender()\u0027s locking and adjust accordingly.",
